biz.onomato.frskydash.domain

Class Channel

  • java.lang.Object
    • biz.onomato.frskydash.domain.Channel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Comparator<Channel>

    public class Channel
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Comparator<Channel>
    A Channel is a value that can be updated through the Telemetry protocol. The intention is to use this in a generic way for both Analog values (AD1 and AD2), signal values (RSSI) and hub data. Channels support averaging, and scaling
    Author:
    Espen Solbu

      • toVoiceString

        public java.lang.String toVoiceString()
        Used to concatenate different parameters of the channel to a string that can be used for TextToSpeech. Will convert the value of the channel to Locale.US as that is currently the hardcoded locale for the TextToSpeech engine.
        Returns:
        the string to be passed to the speaker
